"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759747","Department of Health","false","2017-09-18","<p>It is expected that all prisons have access to a full range of health professionals as per services within the community.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2013, NHS England has been responsible for commissioning all healthcare services for prisoners in England. Services are commissioned for individual prisons by NHS England’s local commissioners, based on a local health needs assessment which informs the provision of services required.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has commissioned a report looking at the workforce, market management and recruitment and retention in the adult prison estate in England, to support providers in their recruitment approaches.</p><p> </p><p>The information on the number of National Health Service staff seconded to, and the number of full time general practitioners working in the prison health system is not collected centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","10209 ; 10227","2017-09-18T14:23:13.9Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759747/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759747/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-12","Health Services: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS staff are seconded to the prison health system.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","10210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759748","Department of Health","false","2017-09-18","<p>The National Health Service Constitution states that patients are responsible for keeping appointments or cancelling them within a reasonable time. At present there are no sanctions available for general practitioner practices to manage repeated failure to attend appointments. There are no plans at present to review this.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2017-09-18T13:38:21.763Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759748/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759748/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759748/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-12","General Practitioners: Attendance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to review the sanctions available to GP practices against patients who repeatedly do not attend appointments.","false","Biography information for Iain Stewart","Milton Keynes South","Iain Stewart","10282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759749","Department of Health","false","2017-10-09","<p>NHS Digital publishes quarterly data on turnover of staff working in the National Health Service in England.</p><p> </p><p>82.9% of nurses who were employed by the NHS in full time position in May 2016 were identified as employed by the NHS in a full-time position in May 2017.</p><p> </p><p>85.6% of nurses who were employed by the NHS in full time position in May 2010 were identified as employed by the NHS in a full-time position in May 2011.</p><p> </p><p>Data prior to 2009 is not available.</p><p> </p><p>Source: NHS Digital, Provisional NHS Hospital and Community Health Service monthly workforce statistics</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-10-09T14:33:51.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759749/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759749/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759749/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-12","Nurses: Labour Turnover","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what percentage of nurses employed by the NHS in full-time positions 12 months ago remain in full-time employment in the NHS today; and what the retention rates for full-time nursing staff in (a) 2000, (b) 2005 and (c) 2010.","false","Biography information for Danielle Rowley","Midlothian","Danielle Rowley","10305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759750","Department of Health","false","2017-09-18","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-09-18T12:47:57.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759750/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759750/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-09-12","Hospitals: Attendance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the cost to the NHS of patients who do not attend hospital appointments in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Iain Stewart","Milton Keynes South","Iain Stewart","10281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759751","Home Office","false","2017-10-04","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>Since 8 April 2015 departure data has been collected on all scheduled commercial services departing the UK from air and sea ports and from international rail stations except those services not within the scope of the exit checks programme.</p><p> </p><p>Border Force hold data for outbound alerts issued by Border Force at the National Border Targeting Centre (NBTC) where feedback has been received, such as those which have been progressed for pre-departure intervention.</p><p> </p><p>A variety of agencies, including Border Force, undertake outbound interventions, as a result of this various activity there is no single record held on their respective outcomes.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-04T13:26:39.347Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759751/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759751/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Borders: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many exit checks were conducted at each UK border point of exit in each of the last 12 months; and how many of those checks resulted in (a) temporary and (b) permanent detention by police or other authorities.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","10280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759752","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>Border Force does not release port-specific staffing numbers for national security reasons.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","10311","2017-09-18T15:34:07.583Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759752/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759752/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759752/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration Controls: Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many UK Border Force officers were deployed to Heathrow Airport in each month between August 2016 and August 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","10312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759753","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>Border Force does not release port-specific staffing numbers for national security reasons.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","10312","2017-09-18T15:34:07.503Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759753/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759753/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759753/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration Controls: Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of UK Border Force officers deployed to Heathrow Airport were absent on each day in August 2017.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","10311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759754","Home Office","false","2017-09-20","<p>I recently wrote to all Police and Crime Commissioners and Chief Constables setting out a programme of engagement to better understand the impact of changing demands on the sector and what more can be done to improve productivity and efficiency. As part of this engagement I will be speaking to the Mayor of Greater Manchester.</p><p>The Government protected overall police spending in the 2015 Spending Review, and the 2017/18 police funding settlement maintains that commitment. The Greater Manchester Mayor’s direct resource funding for his Police &amp; Crime Commissioner functions (including council tax precept) is £545.4 million in 2017/18, an increase of £4.2 million on funding levels for 2015/16. It is a matter for Chief Constables, working with their Police and Crime Commissioners, to manage their available resources according to local priorities.</p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on the size of the police workforce at police force area level, the latest of which are available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-workforce-england-and-wales-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-workforce-england-and-wales-31-march-2017</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","10101","2017-09-20T13:28:00.29Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759754/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759754/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759754/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Police: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent discussions she has had with the Greater Manchester Police and Crime Commissioner and the Mayor of Greater Manchester on the level of police resources provided to that city region.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","10100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759755","Home Office","false","2017-09-20","<p>I recently wrote to all Police and Crime Commissioners and Chief Constables setting out a programme of engagement to better understand the impact of changing demands on the sector and what more can be done to improve productivity and efficiency. As part of this engagement I will be speaking to the Mayor of Greater Manchester.</p><p>The Government protected overall police spending in the 2015 Spending Review, and the 2017/18 police funding settlement maintains that commitment. The Greater Manchester Mayor’s direct resource funding for his Police &amp; Crime Commissioner functions (including council tax precept) is £545.4 million in 2017/18, an increase of £4.2 million on funding levels for 2015/16. It is a matter for Chief Constables, working with their Police and Crime Commissioners, to manage their available resources according to local priorities.</p><p>The Home Office collects and publishes data on the size of the police workforce at police force area level, the latest of which are available here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-workforce-england-and-wales-31-march-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/police-workforce-england-and-wales-31-march-2017</a></p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","10100","2017-09-20T13:28:00.35Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759755/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759755/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Police: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she has made an assessment of any correlation between changes to levels of funding for police officers and police and community support officers in (a) Greater Manchester, (b) the Stockport division and (c) the Tameside division on trends in crime statistics for the most recent period covering those areas.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","10101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759756","Home Office","false","2017-09-20","<p>Home Office Ministers have regular meetings as part of the process of policy development and delivery. I expect to engage with all Police and Crime Commissioners and Chief Constables, including the Mayor of Greater Manchester, to discuss my programme to better understand the impact of changing demands on the sector and what more can be done to improve productivity and efficiency.</p><p>I am also happy to meet with Members of Parliament to discuss local policing issues at their request.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","10206","2017-09-20T14:01:54.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759756/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759756/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Police: Stockport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will meet the hon. Members for Denton and Reddish and for Stockport to discuss central government police resourcing for the Stockport division.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","10102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759757","Home Office","false","2017-09-19","<p>I refer the Hon Member to the answer given on the 19th September 2017 to UIN 9894</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-19T15:09:05.857Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759757/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759757/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people have been classified as having no recourse to public funds in (a) Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle constituency, (b) Hull City Council area and (c) the East Riding of Yorkshire Council area in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","10103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759758","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>There are a total of 69 ePassport gates across the 4 Heathrow terminals:</p><p> </p><p>Terminal 2 = 15</p><p>Terminal 3 = 15</p><p>Terminal 4 = 10</p><p>Terminal 5 = 24 in main arrivals hall and 5 in International/Domestic Transfer area</p><p> </p><p>An average of 1 million passengers use the eGates every month, across Heathrow, which is 79.4% of the total number of passengers who are eligible. Whilst the number of eGates open is demand led, current performance addresses volume of passengers with very limited wait times.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","10156","2017-09-18T15:47:01.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759758/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759758/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration Controls: Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many ePassport gates there are in each terminal at Heathrow Airport; and what proportion of those gates were operational in each month between August 2016 and August 2017.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","10155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759759","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>There are a total of 69 ePassport gates across the 4 Heathrow terminals:</p><p> </p><p>Terminal 2 = 15</p><p>Terminal 3 = 15</p><p>Terminal 4 = 10</p><p>Terminal 5 = 24 in main arrivals hall and 5 in International/Domestic Transfer area</p><p> </p><p>An average of 1 million passengers use the eGates every month, across Heathrow, which is 79.4% of the total number of passengers who are eligible. Whilst the number of eGates open is demand led, current performance addresses volume of passengers with very limited wait times.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","10155","2017-09-18T15:47:01.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759759/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759759/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration Controls: Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effect of the use of ePassport gates on queue waiting times at Heathrow Airport.","false","Biography information for Gavin Robinson","Belfast East","Gavin Robinson","10156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759760","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>Your question relates to Home Office income which can be found in the Annual Report and Accounts:</p><p>16-17 Page 117 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/627853/ho_annual_report_and_accounts_2016_2017.pdf</a></p><p>15-16 Page 134 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/539638/HO_AR_16_gov.pdf</a></p><p>14-15 Page 126 – <a href="https://www.gov.uk/mwg-internal/de5fs23hu73ds/progress?id=tNys4lKDcM-N1kzOo5KUl2WQj0Y5-Oh-71pY3aycKfE,&amp;dl" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/mwg-internal/de5fs23hu73ds/progress?id=tNys4lKDcM-N1kzOo5KUl2WQj0Y5-Oh-71pY3aycKfE,&amp;dl</a></p><p>13-14 Page 111 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321446/ARA_web_enabled_18_June.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/321446/ARA_web_enabled_18_June.pdf</a></p><p>12-13 Page 133 - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210660/Annual_Report_and_Accounts_FINAL_updated_logo.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/210660/Annual_Report_and_Accounts_FINAL_updated_logo.pdf</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T15:43:31.737Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759760/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759760/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department,