"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759761","Home Office","false","2017-09-19","<p>On 4 June 2017 the Prime Minister announced that the Government would review the UK’s counter-terrorism strategy to make sure the police and security services have all the powers and capabilities they need to keep our country safe. This review is ongoing.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben  Wallace",,"2017-09-19T11:43:06.753Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759761/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759761/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Independent Reviewer of Terrorism Legislation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the comments of the Independent Reviewer of Terrorism Legislation, Max Hill QC, published in the Independent newspaper on 19 August 2017, if she will make an assessment of the potential merits of expanding the use of disruptive arrests, charges and sentences as part of the criminal justice response to terror suspects.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","10158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759762","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>The Home Office does not publish this data in the format requested.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T15:34:53.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759762/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759762/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759762/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people with dependents who are resident in (a) Hull West and Hessle constituency, (b) Hull City Council area and (c) East Riding of Yorkshire Council area have been classified as having no recourse to public funds in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Emma Hardy","Kingston upon Hull West and Hessle","Emma Hardy","10090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759763","Home Office","false","2017-10-10","<p>The government could put a system in place to facilitate a SAWS scheme within six months.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-10T08:59:46.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759763/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759763/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759763/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Agriculture: Seasonal Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the length of time required to introduce a new seasonal agricultural workers' scheme.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","10161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759764","Home Office","false","2017-10-09","<p>As part of its commitment to meet the Governments transparency agenda the Home Office publishes the monthly spend with all suppliers in excess of £25,000. As such the information you request is already considered to be in the public domain and can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=home+office+spending+over+%C2%A325%2C000&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=all&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=&amp;commit=Refresh+results" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=home+office+spending+over+%C2%A325%2C000&amp;publication_filter_option=all&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=all&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=&amp;commit=Refresh+results</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-09T09:04:49.18Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759764/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759764/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759764/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Compass Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the total expenditure incurred on the Compass asylum accommodation contract was in 2014-15 and 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","10284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759765","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>Annual statistics on the number of Syrian nationals granted settlement (indefinite leave to enter or remain) are published in settlement table se_03 in the Home Office’s ‘Immigration Statistics, April - June 2017’ <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/list-of-tables#settlement" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-april-to-june-2017/list-of-tables#settlement</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Information on how many Syrian nationals granted settlement are resident in each local authority area is not available.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T15:31:55.267Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759765/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759765/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759765/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Immigration: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many people from Syria have been granted indefinite leave to remain in each of the last 12 months; and how many are resident in each local authority area.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","10279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759766","Home Office","false","2017-10-10","<p>Implementation of the changes made by the Immigration Act 2016 to asylum support under the Immigration and Asylum Act 1999 and to local authority support for migrants without immigration status will involve engagement with local authorities, the devolved administrations and other partners on the preparation of the required regulations. We have not yet made a decision on the timing of this work.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-10T09:09:19.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759766/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759766/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759766/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Asylum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to introduce regulations under the Immigration Act 2016 relating to new support arrangements for individuals or families refused asylum.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","10285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759767","Home Office","false","2017-10-09","<p>The Government has carefully considered the Twelfth Report of the Home Affairs Select Committee and will publish its response in due course.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-09T09:05:00.197Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759767/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759767/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759767/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Asylum: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Answer of 3 April 2017 to Question 69586, when she plans to respond to the Home Affairs Select Committee report, Asylum accommodation, published on 17 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Stuart C. McDonald","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Stuart C. McDonald","10302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759768","Home Office","false","2017-09-20","<p>Home Office Ministers have regular meetings as part of the process of policy development and delivery. I expect to engage with all Police and Crime Commissioners and Chief Constables, including the Mayor of Greater Manchester, to discuss my programme to better understand the impact of changing demands on the sector and what more can be done to improve productivity and efficiency.</p><p>I am also happy to meet with Members of Parliament to discuss local policing issues at their request.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","10102","2017-09-20T14:01:54.203Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759768/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759768/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759768/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Police: Tameside","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will meet with the hon. Member for Denton and Reddish, the hon. Member for Stalybridge and Hyde and the hon. Member for Ashton under Lyne to discuss central government police resourcing to the Tameside division.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","10206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759769","Home Office","false","2017-10-09","<p>Whether a person is stateless is a matter of fact and law. Therefore, each case needs to be considered on its facts. It is open to a person to apply for leave to remain as a stateless person. This cannot be done at the same time as an asylum claim is being pursued.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-10-09T09:04:24.33Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759769/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759769/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759769/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Rohingya: Burma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make it her policy to classify members of the Rohingya community as stateless in respect of applications for asylum.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","10189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759770","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at the following address: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T15:35:52.607Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759770/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759770/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759770/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Visas: Abu Dhabi and South Asia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken was to process entry clearance applications for a (a) spouse and (b) fiancé at visa offices in (i) New Delhi, (ii) Mumbai, (iii) Chennai, (iv) Islamabad, (v) Dhaka and (vi) Abu Dhabi in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","10257"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759771","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at the following address: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T15:37:58.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759771/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759771/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759771/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Visas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many entry clearance applications for a (a) spouse and (b) fiancé have not been processed within 12 weeks in each of the last 12 months; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","10258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759772","Home Office","false","2017-09-18","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on visa processing times, including the percentage of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at the following address: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/migration-transparency-data</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-18T15:39:45.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759772/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759772/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759772/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Visas: Abu Dhabi and South Asia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the average time taken was to process priority entry clearance applications for a (a) spouse and (b) fiancé at visa offices in (a) New Delhi, (b) Mumbai, (c) Chennai, (d) Islamabad, (e) Dhaka and (f) Abu Dhabi in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","10259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759773","Home Office","false","2017-11-23","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on the numbers of visas processed is published online at the following address:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-operations-transparency-data-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-operations-transparency-data-august-2017</a> (then listed by publication date under ‘UK Visas &amp; Immigration’).</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-11-23T17:43:49.603Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759773/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759773/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759773/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Visas: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many settlement applications were processed by Sheffield Visa Section between May and August 2016.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","10260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759774","Home Office","false","2017-09-20","<p>The specific data requested is not published by the Home Office.</p><p> </p><p>Published data on the numbers of visas processed within published service standards, is published online at the following address: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-operations-transparency-data-august-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/international-operations-transparency-data-august-2017</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-09-20T13:30:55.327Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759774/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759774/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/759774/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-09-12","Visas: Sheffield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many settlement applications were processed by Sheffield Visa Section between May and August 2017.","false","Biography information for Mike Gapes","Ilford South","Mike Gapes","10261"
